{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Christopher et al.",
    "developed a CNN model that achieved an AUC of 0.945 for detecting glaucoma based on OCT images of the optic nerve head and retinal nerve fiber layer, demonstrating the potential of AI to enhance the efficiency and accuracy of glaucoma screening (26).",
    "AI models were also developed to analyze visual field tests for glaucoma detection and progress monitoring.",
    "Asaoka et al.",
    "trained a CNN on 1,364 visual field tests and achieved an AUC of 0.926 for detecting glaucoma, with a sensitivity of 92.6% and a specificity of 82.7% (27)."
  ]
}